summary: Can you imagine Steve's face when he finds out that Carol's powers came from the Tesseract?! After all the shit that blue cube...
body: Can you imagine Steve’s face when he finds out that Carol’s powers came from the Tesseract?! After all the shit that blue cube has caused him, to find out it actually did something good by making a strong, kind hearted woman even stronger? A woman who is still good and pure of heart, untainted by the corruption of the infinity stone save for her powers which she uses for good. If Steve sheds a tear, no one needs to know.

summary: I can't believe that I went to see Captain Marvel today. It was so good! I loved how empowering she was. Truly a strong...
body:
I can’t believe that I went to see Captain Marvel today. It was so good! I loved how empowering she was. Truly a strong independent woman. But the scene I loved the most was when she told Jude Law’s character that she doesn’t have to prove anything to him and straight off blasted him.

Overall I had so much fun watching it and I was blown away by the visual effects, costumes, story line and I loved the chemistry between her and Fury. (finally we saw other side of Fury (with the cat 😍👌))

But what got to me the most- Avengers Theme with Stan Lee only (I had tears in my eyes) and the post credit scenes - the 1st one got me on the edge of my seat (steve looked so good 🔥 and the plot twist in it) and the 2nd one - I can’t believe that I just waited 10 minutes to see a cat puke a tesseract out of it’s mouth.
